   <body>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA"><a name="DUCc72bb6b82aff10058066a1973a55c3d2"></a>Refitting the rear brake calliper
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4535"> </a>If the brake hoses (2) are replaced or if one of the rear brake system components has been removed, make sure that the hose
            unions on the master cylinder and the calliper are correctly positioned.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="Attenzione"><img class="Attenzione" width="28" height="25" style="display: inline; float: none; left: 0.0; text-align: left; top: 0.0;" src="img/warning.jpg">Warning
      </div>
      <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4538"> </a>A wrongly routed hose may lead to brake system failure and hinder motorcycle moving parts correct operation. Comply with the
         aiming shown in the figure.
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_041804545.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4543"> </a>Remember to fit the copper sealing washers&nbsp;(3) to the union when reconnecting the brake hose to the brake calliper (5).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4545"> </a>After orientating the union, tighten the special screw (1) to 23 Nm ±10%.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4547"> </a>If the speed sensor (6) was removed, fit it on the calliper holder plate (A) with the spacer (8) and tighten the screw (7)
            to the&nbsp;torque of 10 Nm ±10%.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="Attenzione"><img class="Attenzione" width="28" height="25" style="display: inline; float: none; left: 0.0; text-align: left; top: 0.0;" src="img/note.jpg">Note
      </div>
      <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4550"> </a>The gap between sensor and the brake disc retaining screw must be between 0.6 and 2.2 mm.
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4553"> </a>If calliper holder plate (A) was removed, refer to Section "<a href="80809.html#DUCfed430602b7510058c3987d9909970d2">Removing the rear wheel eccentric hub and the rear wheel shaft</a>" for more details on its reassembly.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4558"> </a>Insert the rear brake calliper (5) on the brake disc, aligning it with the holes of the calliper holder plate (A).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4560"> </a>Apply recommended grease on screws (4) and tighten them to a torque of 25 Nm ±5%.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_006803182.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4565"> </a>For position of hose (2), speed sensor (6) and hose clips, comply with the provisions under Section "<a href="78699.html#DUC690d85c02b1310058c6793c8b30eb8d2">Routing wiring harnesses / hoses</a>" for the base version or under Section "<a href="78701.html#DUCba4d95002b1410058c6b93c8b30eb8d2">Routing wiring harnesses / hoses</a>" for the Pikes Peak, Granturismo or Touring versions.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4574"> </a>Fill the rear brake system.
         </div>
      </div>
   </body>
